#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_aos_array.py:78
msgid ""
"When a 1-D array of length *n* is combined with a 2-D array of shape ``(n, "
"k)``, numpy's standard broadcasting would fail because it aligns shapes from "
"the right: ``(n,)`` vs ``(n, k)`` becomes ``(1, n)`` vs ``(n, k)``.  VTK "
"arrays expect per-tuple scalars to broadcast across components, so we "
"reshape ``(n,)`` to ``(n, 1)`` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_aos_array.py:84
msgid ""
"When the 1-D length does **not** match the leading dimension of the other "
"operand (e.g. a reduction result of shape ``(k,)`` against ``(n, k)``), we "
"leave the shapes alone and let numpy handle it with its standard right-"
"aligned broadcasting rules."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/python/vtkmodules/vtkmodules.numpy_interface.vtk_aos_array.md:97
msgid ""
"Bases: {py:obj}`vtkmodules.numpy_interface._vtk_array_mixin."
"VTKDataArrayMixin`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_aos_array.py:102
msgid ""
"VTK stores most numeric data in AOS (array-of-structures) layout: all "
"components of a tuple are contiguous in memory.  This mixin exposes the "
"underlying buffer as a **zero-copy numpy array view**, so that indexing, "
"slicing, and arithmetic work without copying data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_aos_array.py:107
msgid ""
"This mixin is automatically applied to ``vtkAOSDataArrayTemplate`` "
"instantiations and all concrete AOS subclasses (``vtkFloatArray``, "
"``vtkDoubleArray``, ``vtkIntArray``, etc.).  Any AOS array that crosses from "
"C++ to Python is already a ``VTKAOSArray`` instance."
msgstr ""

